<p><b>References</b></p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://ipython.org/ipython-doc/3/interactive/tutorial.html#magic-functions">Jupyter Notebook documentation</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/ipython/ipython/blob/1.x/examples/notebooks/Cell%20Magics.ipynb">The cell magics in IPython</a></li>
</ul>

<p><b>There are two types of magic functions to distinguish:</b></p>

<ul>
  <li><b>Line magics</b>: These are commands preceded by a <code>%</code> character and whose arguments extend only to the end of the current line. For example, <code>%matplotlib inline</code> allows displaying figures directly within the notebook.</li>
  <li><b>Cell magics</b>:  These are commands preceded by the characters <code>%%</code> and will take into account the instructions of the entire cell.</li>
</ul>

